==English==

===Pronunciation===
*dĭp, /dɪp/, /<tt>dIp</tt>/
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɪp|Rhymes: -ɪp]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun|dip|dips}}

#A [[lower]] [[section]] of a [[road]] or [[geological]] [[feature]].
#:''There is a dip in the road ahead.''
#A [[tank]] or [[trough]] where cattle or sheep are immersed in chemicals to kill parasites.
#A [[dip stick]].
#A [[swim]]. (Usually a short swim to refresh).
#:''I'm going for a dip before breakfast.''

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Finnish: [[pulahtaminen]] (3)
*German: [[Senke]] ''f'' (1), [[Absenkung]] ''f'' (1), [[Ölmeßstab]] ''m'' (3)
{{mid}}
{{bottom}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|dip|dips|dipped|dipping}}

#To [[lower]] into a [[liquid]].
#:''Dip your biscuit into your tea''.
#To [[lower]] a [[light]]'s [[beam]].
#:''Dip your lights as you meet an oncoming car.''
#To [[treat]] [[cattle]] or [[sheep]] by [[immersion]] in [[chemical]] [[solution]].
#:''The farmer is going to dip the cattle today.''
#To use a [[dip stick]] to [[check]] [[oil]] level in an [[engine]].

